  "instructions": [
    "Heat the oil in the bottom of a large clay or ceramic tagine over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until softened, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the chicken to the pot and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the spices, cumin, smoked paprika, and cayenne pepper, and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the chicken broth, diced tomatoes, apricots, dates, and almond flour, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer, then reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 25-30 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened.",
    "Stir in the parsley and season with salt to taste.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired.",
    "Serve with crusty bread or couscous, if desired."
  ],
